  "prompt": "How do you convert gallons to ounces?",
  "response": "To convert gallons to ounces, you need to understand the relationship between these two units of volume. Here\u2019s the step-by-step process:\n\n1. **Understand the Conversion Factor**:\n   - **1 gallon** is equal to **128 ounces** in the US customary system.\n\n2. **Set Up the Conversion**:\n   - Multiply the number of gallons by 128 to find the equivalent number of ounces.\n\n3. **Perform the Calculation**:\n   - The formula is:\n     \\[\n     \\text{Ounces} = \\text{Gallons} \\times 128\n     \\]\n\n4. **Example**:\n   - Suppose you want to convert **3 gallons** to ounces.\n   - Using the formula:\n     \\[\n     \\text{Ounces} = 3 \\times 128 = 384 \\text{ ounces}\n     \\]\n\n\\boxed{\\text{Ounces} = \\text{Gallons} \\times 128}",
